Two brothers are expected to run for governor and MP in the August 8 elections.Nyeri Governor Nderitu Gachagua, who is from Mathira, has said he will defend his seat. His brother Rigathi Gachagua has declared his interest in the Mathira parliamentary seat.Speaking to Gukena FM on Sunday, Rigathi defended his family for vying for two seats in the county.&ldquo;Some are even asking us whether we have a sister who can vie for Nyeri woman representative since they have realised we are very hardworking people,&rdquo; he said.Rigathi said he will continue initiating development projects in Mathira, including toilets in schools, for which he has been criticised. Some residents have urged Mathira to focus on more important projects.